<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="71" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d71">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 493.11/471.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Treasury</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-22">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 22, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your Department’s letter of
                            January 10, 1914. relative to payments made by the Chinese Government on
                            account of the Boxer Indemnity for 1913, I have the honor to request
                            that the portion mentioned therein as due the United States,
                            $539,798.06, be retained by your Department, and the amount refundable
                            to China, $543,007.63, be remitted by check, through this Department, to
                            the Charge d’Affaires of China, Washington, D. C.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>